commit.message:
fix: migrate to the typeguard v3.0 API

The latest version of `typeguard` introduced a breaking change that
affected this project.  This commit migrates to the new API, without
maintaining compatibility with the old API.  Existing users may be
forced to upgrade `typeguard` (or reinstall `signature_dispatch`).

commit.message:
feat: check functions in order of priority

This allows the execution order of the overloaded functions to be
controlled, in cases where such control is necessary.

This commit also refactors the core dispatching functionality into its
own function: `signature_dispatch.dispatch()`.  I also decided to expose
this function as part of the public API, because it seems generally
useful.
